    narr:narration """This hub tracks rubric assessments of artifact tailoring, mapping how content is calibrated for specific audiences. The [YC application context](narr:Assessment_Tailoring_YC) remains a primary anchor, driving explicit decisions in the [Scarlet/Dame application](narr:Rubric_Tailoring_ScarletDame), [YC call materials](narr:Rubric_Tailoring_YC_Call), and [investor-facing TAM models](narr:Assess_Tailoring_RevenueModelTAM). A distinct, high-fidelity cluster focuses on the enterprise technical buyer, notably the [Chief Architect persona](narr:Rubric_Tailoring_CustomerArchitect) and the [multi-track pilot plan](narr:Rubric_Tailoring_PilotPlan), which segments messaging across junior developers, sales reps, and executive stakeholders. Internal strategic artifacts, such as [GTM decision-making](narr:RubricAssess_Tailoring_GTM) and [weekly sales calls](narr:RubricAssess_Tailoring_WeeklyCall), demonstrate a shift toward founder-operator and prospect-specific framing. The [overall rubric](narr:Rubric_Assess_Tailoring) acts as a meta-layer, contrasting internal architectural sessions with public-facing content. Efforts to bridge persona gaps are evident in the [dual-persona demo beats](narr:Rubric_Tailoring_YCDemoBeats), which explicitly target the execution team and YC partners.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Assess_Tailoring_RevenueModelTAM> ;
